# Project Rules for AI Agents

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript strictly; avoid `any` unless necessary
- Prefer functional components and hooks in React
- Use meaningful names; keep functions small and focused

## Naming

- Prefer **kebab-case** for file names (e.g. `use-raid-tracker.ts`, `raid-tracker-table/index.tsx`)
- Keep exported symbols idiomatic (e.g. `useRaidTracker` is fine), but keep **file paths** kebab-case
- Avoid oversimplified names for locals and callback params (e.g. `v`, `d`, `c`, `e`); prefer descriptive names like `event`, `nextValue`, `character`, `dungeon`

## Commit Messages

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/):

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>
```

- **feat:** new feature (MINOR)
- **fix:** bug fix (PATCH)
- **docs:** documentation only
- **style:** formatting, no code change
- **refactor:** code change that neither fixes nor adds a feature
- **perf:** performance improvement
- **test:** adding or updating tests
- **chore:** build, CI, tooling
- **BREAKING CHANGE:** use `!` after type/scope or footer (MAJOR)

Example: `feat(auth): add login form`

## Versioning & Changelog

- Use [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/): MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH
- Version lives in `package.json`; shown in the app header via Vite `define` (`AppVersionLabel`)
- When releasing: bump `package.json` version, then add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry
- Changelog entries must describe **actual user-facing changes** included in the release (derived from commits/diff since the previous release), not just “bump version”

### Changelog format

- Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/)
- File: `CHANGELOG.md` at project root
- Sections: `### Added`, `### Changed`, `### Deprecated`, `### Removed`, `### Fixed`, `### Security`
- Entry format: `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`
- Add new entries at the top (above previous releases)
- Do **not** add filler entries like “version bump for release”; if a release contains no notable changes, do not cut a release (or explicitly document why)

### Version bump rules

- **PATCH** — bug fixes, minor tweaks
- **MINOR** — new features, non-breaking changes
- **MAJOR** — breaking changes (use `BREAKING CHANGE` in commit)

## Editing

- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones
- Preserve existing formatting and indentation
- Run linter after changes; fix any new issues

## Project Context

- React 19 + TypeScript + Vite app with Material UI (`@mui/material`, `@mui/icons-material`)
- WoW raid cooldown tracker: characters, dungeons, per-character–dungeon toggles
- Domain state in `useTrackerDomain` (alias `useRaidTracker`); persistence via `storage/index.ts` + `storage/parse.ts` / `storage/persist.ts` (`my-raid-cds` key, `schemaVersion` in saves; persisted snapshot type `PersistedTrackerState`; **current `schemaVersion` is 4**); dungeons list starts empty; corrupted saves reset with a load warning
- BiS lists in separate storage `storage/bis-lists/` (`my-raid-cds-bis-lists` key, `schemaVersion` 1); domain in `useBisListsDomain`; `BisListsProvider` + `useBisListsContext()`; built-in presets in `data/bis-presets/`; local presets editable, built-in read-only (copy via **Save list**)
- Bundled WoW data: `data/wotlk-item-levels.json`, `wotlk-item-names.json` (+ `-ru.json`), `wotlk-item-gear-slots.json`, `raid-loot-by-key.json`; regenerated via `npm run build:wow-data` from `scripts/wowsims-db.json` (`--skip-ru` skips WoWRoad fetch)
- UI locale: `src/i18n/` (`messages/en.ts`, `messages/ru.ts`, `translate.ts`, `localized-domain.ts`, `use-translation.ts`); header **EN**/**RU** toggle drives full UI strings plus item tooltips; `ItemTooltipLocaleProvider` + `useItemTooltipLocale` (same `localStorage` key `my-raid-cds-item-tooltip-locale`); Cavern of Time (en) / WoWRoad (ru) scripts; `hideExternalWowTooltips` on panel/dialog unmount; template raids/specs/classes localized via `localized-domain.ts` + `RaidNames` / `ClassSpecNames`
- Main table UI: `components/raid-tracker-table/` (`RaidTrackerTable`); `CharacterToggleCell` shows gear upgrade hints; sort/search/delete UI state in `use-raid-tracker-table-state.ts`; shared confirm-before-delete in `hooks/use-pending-delete.ts`; toggle helpers in `utils/dungeon-toggles.ts`
- `data/raid-names.ts`, `data/class-specs.ts` (WotLK specs per class, `ClassSpecNames` with `en`/`ru`/`shortEn`/`shortRu`; duplicate spec names like Holy/Frost/Protection/Restoration differ per class), `data/dungeon-list.ts`, `create-template-dungeon.ts` — WotLK template raids (`RaidNames` metadata with `ru`/`en` names, `shortRu`/`shortEn` abbreviations, emblem + `DungeonList`; re-exported from `data/dungeons.ts`)
- Dungeons use `difficulty` (Normal/Heroic); optional `shortName` for compact display; optional `emblem` for display; optional `raidKey` on template rows for bundled raid loot; legacy saves with `mode` are migrated on load; `emblem` loads only from the saved field (template rows include it in `DungeonList`; no raid-name backfill on load); missing `shortName` backfills from `RaidNames` when the name matches on load
- Characters may store optional `mainSpec` / `offSpec` (`{ spec, gearScore? }`) and optional `gearItems` (WowSimsExporter import); legacy v2 saves with flat spec strings or a single `gearScore` migrate on load (`storage/parse.ts`)
- Production `vite.config.ts` uses `manualChunks` for React / MUI vendor splits; Vitest configured in the same file (`test` block, jsdom, `src/test/setup.ts`)
- Tests: Vitest + jsdom + Testing Library; colocated `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx`; shared helpers in `src/test/` (`fixtures.ts`, `render-with-theme.tsx`); CI runs `npm run test:run` after lint
- App version from `package.json` via Vite `define` (`__APP_VERSION__` in `vite-env.d.ts`; label in `app-meta-info`)
- Light/dark mode: `ColorModeProvider` in `contexts/color-mode-provider.tsx` + `useColorMode`; `localStorage` key `my-raid-cds-color-mode`; pre-paint script in `index.html`; CSS vars via `:root[data-color-mode]` in `index.css`
- Sticky header: MUI `AppBar` in `app-header/` (tracker actions, theme toggle, GitHub meta)
- Follow existing patterns; check README before adding dependencies

## Key Behaviors

- **Add from template** — one-shot: loads `DungeonList` only when the dungeon list is empty; `handleAddFromTemplate` no-ops if dungeons already exist (UI hides the action; guard covers other callers)
- **Reset all toggles** — toolbar control clears all cooldown toggles (keeps characters and dungeons)
- **Delete dungeon** — per-row edit and delete icons in the pinned actions column; delete removes that dungeon and its toggles
- **Reset per character** — icon in the character column header clears toggles for that character only
- **Add forms** — only one of character or dungeon form open at a time; submit closes the form; duplicate character (name + class) is rejected; character form accepts optional main/off spec and gear score (WotLK specs for selected class; main and off must differ when both set); dungeon form accepts optional short name (defaults from `RaidNames` when name matches a known raid)
- **Edit character** — edit icon in character column header opens `CharacterEditDialog` to update main/off spec and gear score (name and class unchanged); WowSimsExporter JSON paste imports `gearItems`; `StoredGearItemLine` shows slot/ilvl muted with `WowItemLink` item names styled via `item-link-styles.ts`
- **BiS lists** — toolbar **BiS lists** opens `BisListsPanel`; built-in presets read-only; local presets editable (item IDs per slot, confirm per slot, save/delete); selection drives `getBisSlotMapForCharacter` for upgrade hints
- **Gear upgrade hints** — `CharacterToggleCell` tints toggle background via `evaluateGearUpgradeHint` (equipped gear vs dungeon ilvl tier + optional BiS-filtered raid loot from `raid-loot-by-key.json`)
- **UI locale** — header **EN**/**RU** toggle (`my-raid-cds-item-tooltip-locale`); `useTranslation()` / `t("key")` for UI copy; item links in `wow-item-link` (`item-link-styles.ts`: ilvl-tier color, bold, dotted underline), gear summary, BiS panel follow locale; export and table dungeon/spec labels respect locale
- **Edit dungeon** — edit icon on each dungeon row opens `DungeonEditDialog` to update name, short name, size, mode, and emblem badge (item levels and toggles unchanged)
- **Character column** — shows class icon, name, optional spec icons with compact gear score (`6.6k`, rounded down); tooltip has full spec names
- **Compact table** — below `md`, pinned columns are actions + name only; name cell shows `shortName` when set (full name in tooltip)
- **Export** — filter dungeons with table search, then **Export** in toolbar; one line per visible raid lists characters without CD. Per character: icon checkboxes for main/off spec (when set), or a single checkbox when no specs; format `Name: ShortSpec gs` with `,` between specs and ` / ` between characters (e.g. `ICC25 - Elst: Udk 6.6, Blood 6 / Beta: SP 5.8`; export gear scores omit `k`; see `format-character-export.ts`, `build-export-status.ts`, `format-dungeon-label.ts`)
- **Empty table** — no dungeons: body hint to add or use template; search with no matches: “No dungeons match your search” row (`raid-tracker-table-empty-state`)

## Component Structure

- **kebab-case** for component dirs (e.g. `character-form/`)
- Typical folder: `index.tsx`; add `types.ts` and/or `styles.css` when needed (not every component has all three)
- complex components like `raid-tracker-table/` may include colocated subcomponents (e.g. `dungeon-cells.tsx`, `character-header-cell.tsx`, `raid-tracker-table-head.tsx`, `dungeon-table-row.tsx`, `pinned-column-renderers.tsx`, `use-raid-tracker-table-state.ts`)
- Domain state lives in `useTrackerDomain` (persistence, toggles, deletes, template, `updateCharacter`, `updateDungeon`); `RaidTrackerProvider` + `useRaidTrackerContext()` expose domain to the table and main content. `BisListsProvider` wraps the app for BiS state. `TrackerLayout` composes toolbar (`TrackerControls`), `useTrackerForms`, BiS panel, and export panel state; add-form field state is not in context (avoids re-rendering toolbar/table on keystrokes). Validation in `utils/validate-character.ts` and `utils/validate-dungeon.ts`. `CharacterForm` / `DungeonForm` / `CharacterEditDialog` / `DungeonEditDialog` / `BisListsPanel` stay presentational. `App` mounts providers + `TrackerLayout` only. Ephemeral table UI state (sort, search, pending delete, compact columns) lives in `useRaidTrackerTableState` colocated with the table; edit-character and edit-dungeon dialog state lives in `RaidTrackerTable`. Character name display sx in `utils/character-display.ts`; spec/gear display in `utils/format-character-details.ts` and `components/spec-option-label/`; gear import in `utils/parse-wowsims-exporter.ts`.

